<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2222/7226</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">11 April, 1918</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have communicated to
                            the Acting Secretary of War to-day my decisions concerning aliens
                            drafted into the military service of the United States as follows:<list>
                                <label>I.</label>
                                <item>That both declarants and non-declarants of treaty countries
                                    shall in all cases be promptly discharged upon the request of
                                    the accredited diplomatic representatives of the countries of
                                    which they are citizens.</item>
                                <label>II.</label>
                                <item>That non-declarants of non-treaty countries shall be promptly
                                    discharged upon the request of the Secretary of State, and also
                                    when the War Department is satisfied that a discharge should be
                                    granted in cases where a full and fair hearing has not been
                                    given by the local board.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>